Text.Value: I don't owe anyone.
Leave.
Go on, enjoy yourself. But if any of them sleep past noon they're getting left behind.
If any of your stuff goes missing, just let me know. You're family now.
Just like I'll be glad to be rid of them once we're there.
Go on, enjoy yourself. I've squirreled away a few extra bottles.
I didn't touch the idol. Don't know what happened to it.
But if you mind your manners, maybe I'll remember you when I'm running the Gate.
Here's some free advice: never bargain, just take what's yours.
You're a terrible liar. We had a deal.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated, disappointed - player just lied to her and she saw right through it.

Text.Value: Never been a specialty of mine, no.
What are you doing way over here?
Thanks. See you in Baldur's Gate, I hope. Now scram, before I get emotional.
Somebody stole the idol. If I find out who it was... I'll recruit 'em.

EditorData.NodeContext: exasperated on first line, as she tells us something we gave her was stolen. Beat before final phrase and delivered with a smile - it's a fun line but she's serious about recruiting good thieves
EditorData.logicalname: Gave Idol | Mol doesn't have it.

Text.Value: Sounds more like a challenge than advice. Keep an eye on your pack.

EditorData.NodeContext: frustrated but with a hint of admiration. Last line is a threat to rob us in the future (pack is backpack). We just conned her, but she learned something from us.

Text.Value: Hey, you. Can you keep a secret?
When the barrel's tapped out, I'll be there to save the night. For a price, of course.
I'm not. I'm glad they can celebrate before we've even got to the Gate.
Damn it. Having that stashed away would have made life a lot easier.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated, disappointed. Possible stamp of the foot on 'damn it'. Clenched fists.

Text.Value: Of course. My lips are easily sealed.
Suit yourself.
Watching a bunch of old folks get dumber by the dram-full. And when they run dry...
Here you go. This idol's all yours.
Just between you and me - I nicked some wine.
Fine. Hope the damn thing's cursed.

EditorData.NodeContext: frustrated, but not shouting, as she's dismissed. The 'damn thing' is an idol the player stole and refused to give to her

Text.Value: And now the deal's off. Maybe this will teach you something.
That idol of yours went missing, sorry to say.
And that sounds like the wine drowning your wits.
Fine. Take it.
This party's boring. Should've put me in charge - now, that'd be a real party.
Don't be so harsh on your elders.
Indeed - and now you owe me.
You came through for us. That's a change from most adults I know.
I've got a few bottles tucked away to keep things flowing. For a price, of course.
That sounded dangerously close to a compliment.

Synopsis: Mol the kid leader is standing on the beach far enough from the bulk of the festivities.
